{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, prefix characters are usually unnecessary as the prompt and completion are distinguished.",
    "Rather than using the prefix characters, simply starting the completion with a whitespace character would produce better results due to the tokenisation of GPT models.",
    "In addition, this method can be economical as it reduces the number of unnecessary tokens in the GPT model, where fees are charged based on the number of tokens.",
    "We note that the maximum number of tokens in a single prompt-completion is 4097, and thus, counting tokens is important for effective prompt engineering; e.g., we used the python library 'titoken' to test the tokenizer of GPT series models.",
    "After pre-processing, the splitting process of train, validation, and test set was conducted with the same random seed and ratio used in previous studies, that is, the training/validation set is used for fine-tuning GPT models and test set for confirming their general performances."
  ]
}